info.name: ForgeRock OBRI Sample - V3.0
info.description:
## Postman collection  
ForgeRock offers you a way to play with the Open Banking API via Postman.

You will need to download the postman collection and the according environment variables.
This web site gives you an overview of our collection and a way to stay up to date with it. Enjoy!

item.name: Setup your environment
item.description:
Before running the examples, you will need to load all the environment variables related to the ASPSP.
Instead of having them hardcoded, we choose to load them from the discovery endpoints.

What you need to do is to simple call the two discovery endpoints. This will load your environment to be ready to use the examples!

header.description: Tells all caching mechanisms from server to client whether they may cache this object. It is measured in seconds

header.name: Content-Type
header.description: The mime type of this content

header.name: Date
header.description: The date and time that the message was sent

header.name: Expires
header.description: Gives the date/time after which the response is considered stale

header.name: Pragma
header.description: Implementation-specific headers that may have various effects anywhere along the request-response chain.

header.name: Strict-Transport-Security
header.description: A HSTS Policy informing the HTTP client how long to cache the HTTPS only policy and whether this applies to subdomains.

header.name: X-Content-Type-Options
header.description: The only defined value, "nosniff", prevents Internet Explorer from MIME-sniffing a response away from the declared content-type

header.name: X-Frame-Options
header.description: Clickjacking protection: "deny" - no rendering within a frame, "sameorigin" - no rendering if origin mismatch

header.name: X-XSS-Protection
header.description: Cross-site scripting (XSS) filter

header.name: transfer-encoding
header.description: The form of encoding used to safely transfer the entity to the user. Currently defined methods are: chunked, compress, deflate, gzip, identity.

header.name: x-fapi-interaction-id
header.description: Custom header

item.name: RS test MATLS with PORT (postman bug)

request.description:
Due to postman bug https://github.com/postmanlabs/postman-app-support/issues/4707 
we need to setup the RS domain twice to workaround it.
This request is here to help you testing you did setup the certs for the RS for both with and without port 443.

item.name: Refresh Access token - OB Official API

request.description:
When you do the AISP flow, you will receive an access token. This token as a relatively short period of life and that's normal.
What's expected to you, when your access token is expired and you want to keep accessing the account data of the PSU, is to refresh it.

For that, use the following flow that will allow you to retrieve a new access token, using the refresh token you received during the code exchange.
